                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>30 foot or 60 foot if the tormented is at 125 HP or lower.</p>\n<p>The psychic agony of a tormented spills into the world around them, inflicting murderous hallucinations replicating the tormented's last moments. A non-undead creature that ends its turn in the aura must succeed at a @Check[type:will|dc:32] save or take @Damage[8d4[bleed]]. The creature doesn't take the persistent damage this turn, nor does it get its flat check to end the damage. While it has a condition from Tortured Gaze, a creature can't gain a new condition from the aura but can take damage from it again.</p>"
                },
